      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SPORTING RAGE (5) filled a minor placing at this track two runs ago before finishing second at his latest appearance over 1650m at Bendigo, beaten 4 metres. Finds a nice race and can play a significant role. HURRICANE HOOLY (3) was responsible for a good effort at her latest appearance to get home by a narrow margin over 1650m at Bendigo on July 1. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. Meets a comparable field so she can certainly win again. MEGAWATTS (7) was out of the money first-up two runs ago then overcame a break to get the prize by 6 metres over 2190m at Mildura a week-and-a-half ago. It doesn't get any easier but she is going well enough to be competitive. MYRTLE MAY (1) could only finish sixth over 2150m at Bendigo most recently. Open to improvement and is in the mix.",
